Control Flow in Python


Control flow lets your program make decisions and repeat actions.

ğŸ“Œ 
if
 Statement


Used to make decisions.

age = 18
if age >= 18:
    print("You can vote!")
else:
    print("You are too young to vote.")
ğŸ” for Loop

Used to repeat a block of code a specific number of times.

for i in range(5):
    print("Hello!")  # Prints "Hello!" five times
ğŸ” while Loop


Repeats code as long as a condition is true.

count = 0
while count < 3:
    print("Counting:", count)
    count += 1
